textAnnotation.text: The process is initiated when a hardware issue of a device is detected. To be able to get services, the user needs to have an account. If a user is new, he/she creates an account at the first step. Then, he/she logs in to the system with the provided credentials during the account creation process. If the login was not successful, the user is asked to re-enter the correct credentials until the login is successful. When the user is logged into the system, he/she should enter the model of his/her Smartphone to proceed with the next step. Then, the user is asked to select the type of hardware issue from a drop-down list box. Based on the selected issue, the system prepares and lists the required materials and tools for the reparation process. At the same time, the system offers some ordering options for the listed materials and tools to the user. In this stage, the user has two options. The first option is to skip this process if the user already has all the listed requirements and there is no need to get them through the system. The second option is taken when the user has none or part of the listed tools and materials. In this case, the user could get second-hand tools and materials at a reasonable price from his/her friends existing in his/her contact list within the system and in case of unavailability purchase the rest of them from the offered options by the system. At the next step, the reparation instructions are automatically displayed to the user by the system and the user repair the device accordingly. It is important to mention that Manual has been selected as the type of this task since the user does the reparation task by hand without any interaction with the system. After reparation, if the reparation task was successful, the user could write a review and/or upload a video taken from the reparation steps, or totally skip these two tasks. On the other hand, if the issue was not fixed, the user needs to take or send the device to an expert.
